<br>
it costs about $0.25 per cd to mass produce them.  a new cd can sell for as much as $20, ive seen it, even at best buy, sam goody, etc.  the artist themselves makes about $0.20 per cd sale.  the rest of it goes to the RIAA.<br>
<br>
artists get rich from concerts.  ticket sales, tshirt sales, etc.  thats where artists get their money.  not cd sales.  the artists themselves, i wouldnt doubt, really dont care about who is illegally sharing their songs, because those people that do it ALOT will probably go to concerts, and will ALSO have more money to 1) buy a ticket, 2) buy at least one tshirt, 3) quite possibly buy other concert trinkets, which all becomes money in the artists pocket.<br>
<br>
<br>
i, personally, was burned badly by the crap cds.  heard 3 songs from the album on the radio, liked them, went and bought the cd.  i think it had 12 songs on it, and only those 3 were good.  a shame really, since the band used to put out alot more good music.<br>
<br>
i think the RIAA needs to die, but thats just me.<br>
<br>
